import java.util.Arrays;

public void sortArray(int[] nums) {
    Arrays.sort(nums);
}
```

    The algorithm for each language uses the built-in sorting function provided by the language's standard library to sort the given array of integers in ascending order.

- In C++, the `std::sort` function from the `<algorithm>` library is used.
- In Java, the `Arrays.sort` method from the `java.util` package is used.
- In Python, the in-built `sort` method of the list object (nums) is used.
- In JavaScript, the `Array.prototype.sort` method is used with a custom comparator function `(a, b) => a - b` to ensure numeric sorting instead of lexicographic sorting (the default behavior of JavaScript's sort).

All these built-in methods use efficient sorting algorithms underneath, with average-case complexity of O(n log n).
